Iavan Pijoos, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - A three-year-old boy died after his house caught fire in Elsburg, east of Johannesburg, on Friday morning, paramedics said.&nbsp;ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said paramedics had arrived on the scene and found the home in flames.&nbsp;Fire services were already on the scene trying to extinguish the blaze.&nbsp;"Upon inspection, paramedics and firefighters found the body of a three-year-old boy lying in the ruins."The boy was declared dead on the scene.&nbsp;Meiring said the boy's mother had sustained minor injuries.&nbsp;She was treated and transported to a nearby hospital.The cause of the fire was not yet known.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.